definition:
A man of the tribe of Benjamin living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.8.35; 
 son of: Micah (H4318H); 
 brother of: Pithon (H6377), Melech (H4429) and Tarea (H8390); 
 father of: Jehoaddah (H3085)
 § Ahaz = "he has grasped"
1) king of Judah, son Jotham, father of Hezekiah
2) a Benjamite, son of Micah, and great grandson of Jonathan
